[SN]TITLE[SN]
Glyn Baines, 84, is oldest Eisteddfod fine art award winner

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An 84-year-old from Gwynedd has become the oldest winner of the National Eisteddfod's Gold Medal for Fine Art.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Glyn Baines, from Bala,was presented with the award for his collection of abstract collages on Saturday at the National Eisteddfod of Wales in Meifod, Powys.
He also received a cheque for Â£5,000.
Mr Baines left his family's farming business in his 30s to pursue his dream of becoming an artist.
He said: "I like to describe my work as a celebration of colour and life.
"There are seven pieces in total and they all mean a lot to me."
This year's National Eisteddfod runs from from 1-8 August.
